b |url=http://www.uefa.org/MultimediaFiles/Download/Regulations/uefaorg/Regulations/02/16/53/77/2165377_DOWNLOAD.pdf |title=Regulations of the UEFA European Women\u2019s Championship, 2015\u201317 |website=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |year=2017 |access-date=15 June 2017 |format=PDF}}</ref>\n*90 minutes.\n*30 minutes of [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]] if necessary.\n*[[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|Penalty shoot-out]] if scores still level.\n*Maximum of three substitutions, with a fourth allowed in extra time.\n|}\n\n===Statistics===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:100px\" | Statistic<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/womenseuro/season=2017/matches/round=2000626/match=2020924/statistics/index.html |title=UEFA Women's EURO - Netherlands-Denmark - Statistics |website=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=6 August 2017 |access-date=6 August 2017}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:70px\" | Netherlands\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:70px\" | Denmark\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Goals scored\n| 4\n| 2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Total shots\n| 10\n| 11\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Shots on target\n| 7\n| 4\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Saves\n| 1\n| 2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Ball possession\n| 50%\n| 50%\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Corner kicks\n| 0\n| 4\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Fouls committed\n| 16\n| 10\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Offsides\n| 0\n| 2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Yellow cards\n| 3\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Red cards\n| 0\n| 0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.uefa.com/womenseuro/index.html}}\n\n{{UEFA Women's Euro 2017}}\n{{UEFA Women's Championship}}\n\n[[Category:UEFA Women's Euro 2017|Final]]\n[[Category:Netherlands women's national football team matches]]\n[[Category:Denmark women's national football team matches]]\n[[Category:Sport in Enschede]]\n[[Category:August 2017 sports events in Europe]]\n[[Category:Denmark\u2013Netherlands relations]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football match\n| title            = UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Final\n| image            = [[File:Grolsch Veste wedstrijd.JPG|250px]]\n| caption          = [[De Grolsch Veste]] in [[Enschede]] hosted the final.\n| event            = [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017]]\n| team1            = [[Netherlands women's national football team|Netherlands]]\n| team1association = {{flagicon|NED|size=30px}}\n| team1score       = 4\n| team2            = [[Denmark women's national football team|Denmark]]\n| team2association = {{flagicon|DEN|size=30px}}\n| team2score       = 2\n| date             = {{Start date|2017|8|6|df=y}}\n| stadium          = [[De Grolsch Veste]]\n| city             = [[Enschede]]\n| woman_player1    = [[Sherida Spitse]] (Netherlands)<ref name=\"player of the match\">{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/womenseuro/news/newsid=2482469.html |title=Every player of the match at Women's EURO |website=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=6 August 2017 |access-date=6 August 2017}}</ref>\n| referee          = [[Esther Staubli]] ([[Swiss Football Association|Switzerland]])<ref name=\"referees\"/>\n| attendance       = 28,182<ref name=\"attendance\"/>\n| weather          = Partly cloudy<br>{{convert|20|\u00b0C|\u00b0F|abbr=on}}<br>44% [[humidity]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/womenseuro/season=2017/matches/round=2000626/match=2020924/match-info/index.html |title=UEFA Women's EURO - Netherlands-Denmark - Match info |website=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=6 August 2017 |access-date=6 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wunderground.com/history/airport/EHTW/2017/08/06/DailyHistory.html |title=Weather History for Twenthe, Netherlands |website=[[Weather Underground (weather service)|Weather Underground]] |publisher=[[The Weather Company]] |date=6 August 2017 |access-date=6 August 2017}}</ref>\n| previous         = [[UEFA Women's Euro 2013 Final|2013]]\n| next             = ''2021''<!--[[UEFA Women's Euro 2021 Final|2021]]-->\n}}\nThe '''UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Final''' was a [[Association football|football]] match to determine the winner of [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017]]. The match took place on 6 August 2017 at [[De Grolsch Veste]] in [[Enschede]], Netherlands,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/competitions/General/02/42/11/93/2421193_DOWNLOAD.pdf |title=UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Match Schedule |website=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=November 2016 |access-date=15 June 2017}}</ref> and was contested by the winners of the semi-finals, the [[Netherlands women's national football team|Netherlands]] and [[Denmark women's national football team|Denmark]].\n\nThe Netherlands won the final 4\u20132 for their first [[UEFA Women's Championship]] title.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/womenseuro/news/newsid=2491105.html |title=Dutch delight: how the Netherlands won Women's EURO |website=UEFA.com |publisher=[[UEFA|Union of European Football Associations]] |date=6 August 2017 |access-date=6 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/printoutfiles/competitions/woco/2017/E/E_2020924_fr.pdf |title=UEFA Women's Euro 2017 \u2013 Final: Full-time report |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |format=PDF |date=6 August 2017 |access-date=25 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nBoth the Netherlands and Denmark reached the UEFA Women's Championship final for the first time in their histories. For the first time since [[UEFA Women's Euro 1993|1993]], a country other than [[Germany women's national football team|Germany]] won the competition. Apart from Germany, only two other countries have won the championship: Norway and Sweden. Norway was defeated by both the Netherlands and Denmark in the preliminary round whereas Sweden was defeated by the Netherlands in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/printoutfiles/competitions/womenseuro/2017/e/e_2020924_pk.pdf |title=UEFA Women's Euro 2017 \u2013 Final: Match press kits |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |format=PDF |date=6 August 2017 |access-date=25 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe finalists met each other in the group stage of the tournament, with the Netherlands winning 1\u20130 via a penalty from [[Sherida Spitse]].\n\n==Route to the final==\n{{details|UEFA Women's Euro 2017}}\n\n{| style=\"width:100%; text-align:center\"\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#99CCFF\"\n! colspan=\"2\" | Netherlands\n! Round\n! colspan=\"2\" | Denmark\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#C1E0FF\"\n| Opponents\n| Result\n| [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017#Group stage|Group stage]]\n| Opponents\n| Result\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{fbw|NOR}}\n| [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Group A#Netherlands vs Norway|1\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF\" | Match 1\n| align=\"left\" | {{fbw|BEL}}\n| [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Group A#Denmark vs Belgium|1\u20130]]\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{fbw|DEN}}\n| [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Group A#Netherlands vs Denmark|1\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF\" | Match 2\n| align=\"left\" | {{fbw|NED}}\n| [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Group A#Netherlands vs Denmark|0\u20131]]\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{fbw|BEL}}\n| [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Group A#Belgium vs Netherlands|2\u20131]]\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF\" | Match 3\n| align=\"left\" | {{fbw|NOR}}\n| [[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Group A#Norway vs Denmark|1\u20130]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\" | '''[[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Group A|Group A]] winner'''\n<center>{{UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Group A table|only_pld_pts=yes|showteam=NED}}</center>\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF\" | Final standings\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\" | '''[[UEFA Women's Euro 2017 Group A|Group A]] runner-up'''\n<center>{{UEFA Women's