es              = \n}}\n\n'''Santpur''' is a town and market center in [[Chandrapur Municipality]] in [[Rautahat District]] in the [[Narayani Zone]] of south-eastern [[Nepal]]. The formerly [[Village development committee (Nepal)|village development committee]] was merged to form the municipality on 18 May 2014. At the time of the [[1991 Nepal census]] it had a population of 5594.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.digitalhimalaya.com/collections/nepalcensus/form.php?selection=1|title=Nepal Census 2001|work=Nepal's Village Development Committees|publisher=[[Digital Himalaya]]|accessdate=29 November 2008 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{coord|27|5|N|85|21|E|source:plwiki|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Rautahat District]]\n\n\n{{Narayani-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Pegship", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2013{{Narayani-geo-stub}}, +{{Province2NP-geo-stub}} usingStubSorter", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santpur"}
{"title_page": "FK Sileks", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club |\n  clubname = Sileks |\n  image = FK Sileks logo.svg|\n  upright  = 0.8|\n  fullname = Fudbalski klub Sileks Kratovo|\n  nickname = \u041a\u0440\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0446\u0438 (Kratovo Boys)|\n  founded  = {{Start date and age|1965}} |\n  ground   = [[Gradski stadion Kratovo|Gradski stadion Sileks]]|\n  capacity = 1,800 |\n  chairman = Stojan Milanov|\n  manager  = Momchilo Mitevski|\n  league   = [[Macedonian First Football League|Macedonian First League]]{{Flagicon|Macedonia}} |\n  season   = [[2018\u201319 Macedonian First Football League|2018\u201319]] |\n  position = 8th |\n pattern_la1=_red_stripes|pattern_b1=_red_stripes|pattern_ra1=_red_stripes|pattern_sh1=|pattern_so1=|\n  leftarm1=0000AA|body1=0000AA|rightarm1=0000AA|shorts1=0000AA|socks1=CC0000|\n  pattern_la2=_whiteshoulders|pattern_b2=_whiteshoulders|pattern_ra2=_whiteshoulders|\n  leftarm2=FFFFFF|body2=FFFFFF||rightarm2=FFFFFF|shorts2=FFFFFF|socks2=CC0000|\n}}\n\n'''FK Sileks''' ({{lang-mk|\u0424\u041a \u0421\u0438\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441}}) is a [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Kratovo, North Macedonia|Kratovo]], [[North Macedonia]] who play in the [[Macedonian First Football League|Macedonian First League]].\n\n==History==\nThe club was founded in 1965.\n\nSileks biggest accomplishment in 90s came in the [[1989\u201390 Yugoslav Cup|Cup]] where they reached the quarter-finals. It was a remarkable achievement considering they defeated both Sarajevo teams, [[FK \u017deljezni\u010dar Sarajevo|FK \u017deljezni\u010dar]] and [[FK Sarajevo]] in back to back rounds, and they were both top-league sides at that time. Since the formation of the [[First Macedonian Football League]], they played at top level from the start until their relegation in 2013. Their biggest success happened during the 1990s, when they won three league titles (including a record five time runners-up) and two national cups.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rsssf.com/tablesf/fyromhist.html#93|title=Macedonia&nbsp;\u2013 List of Final Tables|work=Igor Kramarsic and Goran Mancevski|first=|last=}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n'''{{Flagicon|Macedonia}} [[Macedonian First Football League|Macedonian First League]]:'''\n*'''Winners (3):''' [[1995\u201396 Macedonian First Football League|1995\u201396]], [[1996\u201397 Macedonian First Football League|1996\u201397]], [[1997\u201398 Macedonian First Football League|1997\u201398]]\n*Runners-up (5): [[1992\u201393 Macedonian First Football League|1992\u201393]], [[1993\u201394 Macedonian First Football League|1993\u201394]], [[1994\u201395 Macedonian First Football League|1994\u201395]], [[1998\u201399 Macedonian First Football League|1998\u201399]], [[2003\u201304 Macedonian First Football League|2003\u201304]]\n\n'''{{Flagicon|Macedonia}} [[Macedonian Second Football League|Macedonian Second League]]:'''\n*'''Winners (1):''' [[2013\u201314 Macedonian Second Football League|2013\u201314]]\n\n'''{{Flagicon|SR Macedonia}} Macedonian Republic Cup:'''\n*'''Winners (2):''' 1988\u201389, 1989\u201390\n\n'''{{Flagicon|Macedonia}} [[Macedonian Football Cup]]:'''\n*'''Winners (2):''' [[1993\u201394 Macedonian Football Cup|1993\u201394]], [[1996\u201397 Macedonian Football Cup|1996\u201397]]\n*Runners-up (1): [[1994\u201395 Macedonian Football Cup|1994\u201395]]\n\n==Recent seasons==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:100%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=9|League\n!rowspan=2 width=\"30\"|[[Macedonian Football Cup|Cup]]\n!rowspan=2 colspan=2 width=\"200\"|[[UEFA#Competitions|European competitions]]\n|-\n!Division\n!width=\"25\"|P\n!width=\"25\"|W\n!width=\"25\"|D\n!width=\"25\"|L\n!width=\"25\"|F\n!width=\"25\"|A\n!width=\"25\"|Pts\n!width=\"40\"|Pos\n|-\n|1992\u201393\n|[[1992\u201393 Macedonian First Football League|1. MFL]]\n|34\n|17\n|6\n|11\n|72\n|50\n|40\n|bgcolor=\"silver\"|2nd\n|\n|\n|\n|-bgcolor=#EEEEEE\n|1993\u201394\n|[[1993\u201394 Macedonian First Football L