5\u043a\u0441}}) is a [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Kratovo, North Macedonia|Kratovo]], [[North Macedonia]] who play in the [[Macedonian First Football League|Macedonian First League]].\n\n==History==\nThe club was founded in 1965.\n\nSileks biggest accomplishment in 90s came in the [[1989\u201390 Yugoslav Cup|Cup]] where they reached the quarter-finals. It was a remarkable achievement considering they defeated both Sarajevo teams, [[FK \u017deljezni\u010dar Sarajevo|FK \u017deljezni\u010dar]] and [[FK Sarajevo]] in back to back rounds, and they were both top-league sides at that time. Since the formation of the [[First Macedonian Football League]], they played at top level from the start until their relegation in 2013. Their biggest success happened during the 1990s, when they won three league titles (including a record five time runners-up) and two national cups.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rsssf.com/tablesf/fyromhist.html#93|title=Macedonia&nbsp;\u2013 List of Final Tables|work=Igor Kramarsic and Goran Mancevski|first=|last=}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n'''{{Flagicon|Macedonia}} [[Macedonian First Football League|Macedonian First League]]:'''\n*'''Winners (3):''' [[1995\u201396 Macedonian First Football League|1995\u201396]], [[1996\u201397 Macedonian First Football League|1996\u201397]], [[1997\u201398 Macedonian First Football League|1997\u201398]]\n*Runners-up (5): [[1992\u201393 Macedonian First Football League|1992\u201393]], [[1993\u201394 Macedonian First Football League|1993\u201394]], [[1994\u201395 Macedonian First Football League|1994\u201395]], [[1998\u201399 Macedonian First Football League|1998\u201399]], [[2003\u201304 Macedonian First Football League|2003\u201304]]\n\n'''{{Flagicon|Macedonia}} [[Macedonian Second Football League|Macedonian Second League]]:'''\n*'''Winners (1):''' [[2013\u201314 Macedonian Second Football League|2013\u201314]]\n\n'''{{Flagicon|SR Macedonia}} Macedonian Republic Cup:'''\n*'''Winners (2):''' 1988\u201389,